<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 06 at 4:32PM EST  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...Patchy Areas of Black Ice Overnight...
Periods of snow showers are expected to continue to impact
portions of the central and northern valley of East Tennessee. A
dusting to 1 inch of snow is possible over the next couple of
hours, north of I-40. With temperatures plummeting in the upper
teens to 20s, any wet spots on roads will turn to patches of ice.
This will create slippery conditions in some spots, especially on
bridges and untreated secondary roads.
Use caution if traveling overnight and Friday morning. Slow down
and allow extra time to reach your destination, and do not assume
that a well traveled roadway will be free of snow or black ice.</description>
